  "text": "There is an open subset W ⊂ k[[t]]⊗ V with the property that for any w ∈ W, and any (u, v) ∈ (N×V ) (λ,µ) (a G-orbit, see [CITATION_1] , Theorem 1), we have µ) is an open embedding. Also, the embedding W × (N × V ) (λ,µ) ֒→Ω (λ,µ) of the orbit closures is an open embedding as well. Hence the Frobenius action on the IC stalks of (N × V ) (λ,µ) is encoded in the polynomials Π (λ ′ ,µ ′ ),(λ,µ) introduced after Proposition 14.",
